		<description><![CDATA[The Executive Board of the Regional Committee for Disaster Management in West Africa Role : prepare the agenda of the annual Regional Consultation on Natural Disaster in West Africa; hold annual meeting of the Regional Executive Committee; submit and follow-up on the action plan. Membership : composed of three representatives &#8230;]]></description>
				<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>The Executive Board of the Regional Committee for Disaster Management in West Africa</p>
<p>Role : prepare the agenda of the annual Regional Consultation on Natural Disaster in West Africa; hold annual meeting of the Regional Executive Committee; submit and follow-up  on the action plan.</p>
<p>Membership : composed of three representatives of Member States and three representatives of Red Cross/Red Crescent National Societies designated by the Regional Committee according to their language groups for a period of one year. Representatives of Red Cross/Red Crescent National Societies shall be from countries different from representatives of Member States. Within each language group (English, French, Portuguese), designation will take place on rotational basis. The President of the Regional Committee shall be elected by members of the Executive Secretariat among representatives of Member States. The President chairs meetings of both the Regional Committee and of the Executive Board.</p>
<p>Support to the Executive Board is provided by ECOWAS, OCHA and IFRC.</p>
]]></content:encoded>
